.TH "clk_disable_regmap" 9 "clk_disable_regmap" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
clk_disable_regmap \- standard disable() for regmap users
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" clk_disable_regmap
.BI "(struct clk_hw *hw "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
clk to operate on
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Clocks that use regmap for their register I/O can set the
enable_reg and enable_mask fields in their struct clk_regmap and then use
this as their \fBdisable\fP operation, saving some code.
